## skymap.svg.tmpl
##
## Renders ONLY the raw <svg>...</svg> markup for $almanac.skymap — nothing
## else (no surrounding <html>, no DOCTYPE) — so the output file is a plain
## SVG document that index.html's pollSkymap() can fetch as text and drop
## straight into the card via wrap.innerHTML, exactly like the snapshot
## that's already embedded in celestial.html.
##
## Same "one template, one job" pattern already used for archive.json.tmpl
## and charts_json.tmpl: a tiny .tmpl whose only output is the one thing a
## page needs, rather than extracting it from a bigger HTML report.
##
## width=700 matches what mapSkymap.php already calls (the real PHP card
## this was adapted from) — kept the same rather than switching to
## width='auto' so the rendered sky stays visually identical to the
## snapshot already on the page. fromoutside isn't passed, so it defaults
## to the "lying on the ground looking up" view — also matching the PHP
## card and the snapshot's own <desc> framing.
##
## bodies / earth_satellites / per-body Formats are NOT passed here on
## purpose — those come from [Almanac][[Skymap]] in weewx.conf, which (per
## the mapSkymap.php output already on this site) is presumably already
## configured the way you want it. Pass them as keyword args here only if
## you want this particular file to differ from your site's normal config.
#errorCatcher Echo
$almanac.skymap(width=300)
